  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5192",
  "title": "Differentiate :focus and :focus-visible styles",
  "body": "When clicking a pagination link in the `Pagination` widget, the link receives the `focus` state, which applies the `:focus` styles while it doesn't necessarily needs it. This is a different use case than tabbing to the link, where those styles are necessary to see where the focus is.\r\n\r\nTo account for this, we could differentiate between `:focus` and [`:focus-visible`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:focus-visible) styles in our themes to avoid applying focus styles on elements which `focus`state doesn't need to be made obvious.\r\n\r\nThe `focus-within` state isn't applied by all browsers, but we can set up [fallbacks](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:focus-visible#selectively_showing_the_focus_indicator) to account for those.",
